      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 1919: loadMissingBodyOverwrites() only stores successful non-empty overwrites. Messages for which the plugin returns no overwrite remain indistinguishable from messages that were never processed, so every later load/reload scans and retransforms the same history again. This can become expensive on large conversations and can repeatedly call plugin code for unchanged messages. Store a sentinel/processed state separately from the overwrite value, or explicitly mark empty results as processed while keeping them out of the API-visible payload.\n```suggestion\n// Example approach: track processed state separately from the displayed value.\nit-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwriteLoaded\"] \u003d \"true\";\nif (!bodyOverwrite.empty())\n    it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d bodyOverwrite;\nelse\n    it-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData.erase(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n```",
